canonical:
  title: 祭妻文 代人行三言
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 云云年二八歸于我壼則閑婦儀雅予所指輒迎迓事舅姑鮮微過謹蒸甞無小惰方艱難同坎坷家稍潤命不假奄爾徂花忽謝天使然無可奈膓已裂淚隨墮酒旣薄盈一斝諒吾誠一啜可嗚呼哀哉
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 祭妻文 代人行三言
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 云云。年二八。歸于我。壼則閑。婦儀雅。予所指。輒迎迓。事舅姑。鮮微過。謹蒸甞。無小惰。方艱難。同坎坷。家稍潤。命不假。奄爾徂。花忽謝。天使然。無可奈。膓已裂。淚隨墮。酒旣薄。盈一斝。諒吾誠。一啜可。嗚呼哀哉。
korean:
  title: 아내에게 제사 지내는 글 다른 사람 대신 행하다 3언구
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 나이 16에 내게 시집와서 집안 일에 익숙하고 부인으로서의 품위가 아담하여 나의 지시하는 일을 어김없이 잘하고, 시부모를 섬기는 데 조그마한 허물도 없었으며, 제사에 삼가 조금도 게으름이 없었도다. 바야흐로 우리가 가난할 때에 함께 험한 일을 많이 당했는데 집이 조금 윤택해지자 명을 빌리지 못하고 문득 가버리니 꽃이 홀연히 졌구나. 하늘이 이렇게 한 것이니 어찌할 수 없도다. 창자가 찢어지고 눈물이 땅에 떨어지노라. 박주나마 한 잔을 채웠으니 내 정성으로 알고 한 번 마시는 것이 좋겠소. 아, 슬프도다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1120_010_0250&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Memorial Offering to My Wife, Performed on Another's Behalf in Tripled Words
  author: Lee Gyubo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    At sixteen she came to my household,
    Skilled in all the ways of our home,
    Graceful in her bearing as a wife should be.
    Whatever I asked of her, she would do without fail,
    Serving my parents with such devotion
    That not the smallest fault could be found.
    In the rituals and offerings, never a moment's negligence—
    Even when hardship came upon us,
    When poverty bent our backs and trials tested us,
    She walked beside me through every rough path.
    Then at last our fortune turned,
    Our house grew warm and full.
    Yet Heaven did not wait.
    She departed like a flower that blooms one dawn
    And withers before the sun sets.
    What Heaven ordains, we cannot refuse.
    My heart is shattered. My tears fall like rain.
    I have only this thin wine to offer,
    One meager cup from what little remains.
    May she know that this comes from my deepest heart—
    Let her drink and know my love endures.
    Alas, what sorrow fills this world.
  footnotes:
    - This memorial text was composed by Lee Gyubo on behalf of another, following the convention of 'tripled words' (삼언구)—likely referring to a specific poetic meter or formulaic structure common in such commemorative pieces.
    - The phrase 'thin wine' (박주) refers to a diluted or humble wine offering, emphasizing both the family's modest circumstances and the sincerity of the gesture despite poverty.
